{
  "texts": [
    "Communicatee typeCommunicatee Type determines which type of agents are assumed to receive messages in a Comm-MADRL system.",
    "We found that in the literature, communicatee type can be classified into the following categories based on whether agents in the environment communicate with each other directly or not.",
    "Agents in the MASIn this category, the set of communicatees consists of agents in the environment, and they directly communicate with each other.",
    "Nevertheless, due to partial observability, agents may not be able to communicate with every agent in the MAS, and thus we further distinguish the types of communicatees as follows:• Nearby Agents.",
    "In many Comm-MADRL systems, communication is only allowed between neighbors."
  ]
}